export const getRandomName = () => {
  const firstNames = [
    'Alice',
    'Bob',
    'Charlie',
    'David',
    'Eve',
    'Frank',
    'Grace',
    'Heidi',
    'Ivan',
    'Judy',
    'Kate',
    'Leo',
    'Mia',
    'Nate',
    'Olivia',
    'Paul',
    'Queenie',
    'Randy',
    'Steve',
    'Tina',
    'Uma',
    'Vivian',
    'Walter',
    'Xenia',
    'Yolanda',
    'Zach',
  ];
  const lastNames = [
    'Smith',
    'Johnson',
    'Williams',
    'Brown',
    'Jones',
    'Garcia',
    'Rodriguez',
    'Lee',
    'Walker',
    'Martinez',
    'Clark',
    'Wilson',
    'Taylor',
    'Moore',
    'Anderson',
    'Thomas',
    'Jackson',
    'White',
    'Harris',
    'Sanchez',
    'Clark',
    'Lewis',
    'Robinson',
    'Turner',
  ];

  const firstName = firstNames[Math.floor(Math.random() * firstNames.length)];
  const lastName = lastNames[Math.floor(Math.random() * lastNames.length)];

  return `${firstName} ${lastName}`;
};
